---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="When NOT to work with us — KKT"
  description="We turn down work where we are not the right partner. Here is when not to call us."
  ogImage="/og/not-for-you.png"
>
  <article class="prose-page">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="prose-header">
        <div class="section-label">When NOT to work with us</div>
        <h1 class="h1-page">When NOT to work with us</h1>
        <p class="lede">
          We turn down work where we are not the right partner. To save your
          time and ours, here is when not to call us.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="prose">
        <div class="rule">
          <div class="rule-num">01</div>
          <div>
            <h2>You are below ~$50M in revenue.</h2>
            <p>
              We work with mid-sized retailers and fuel networks. Below
              that scale, the cost of our delivery model exceeds the
              value we can realistically create for you. There are
              good partners for smaller companies. We are not one of
              them.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rule">
          <div class="rule-num">02</div>
          <div>
            <h2>You want AI strategy without delivery.</h2>
            <p>
              We do not write decks that sit on a shelf. Every
              engagement we accept is shaped to put something operating
              into your business. If you want a slide-led strategy
              with no delivery team, we are not the fit.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rule">
          <div class="rule-num">03</div>
          <div>
            <h2>You have no senior data lead inside the company.</h2>
            <p>
              If we are the only people in the room who care about data
              quality, governance, and adoption, the project will fail
              after we leave. We need a senior counterpart inside your
              organisation — not a champion in name, an actual one with
              authority and time.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rule">
          <div class="rule-num">04</div>
          <div>
            <h2>You need a model in production in four weeks.</h2>
            <p>
              A diagnostic in four weeks — yes. A model running in your
              business and creating measured outcomes in four weeks —
              no. Anyone who promises that is selling you something
              else. We will not.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <blockquote class="rule-pull">
          <p>
            Anyone who promises an AI model in production in four weeks
            is selling you something else.
          </p>
        </blockquote>

        <div class="rule">
          <div class="rule-num">05</div>
          <div>
            <h2>You are in heavily regulated banking, public sector, or defence.</h2>
            <p>
              These domains have their own delivery patterns and
              compliance bars. We respect them; we do not pretend to be
              experts in them. There are firms built specifically for
              that work, and you should hire one of them.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rule">
          <div class="rule-num">06</div>
          <div>
            <h2>You want a generic AI vendor.</h2>
            <p>
              If your goal is &ldquo;deploy a chatbot&rdquo;,
              &ldquo;roll out Copilot&rdquo;, or &ldquo;do an LLM
              pilot&rdquo; without a clear business outcome — we are
              the wrong call. We do not do AI for AI&rsquo;s sake. We
              do data, models, and AI where they earn their place
              against margin, cash, availability, customer value, or
              productivity.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="rule">
          <div class="rule-num">07</div>
          <div>
            <h2>You are looking for a body shop.</h2>
            <p>
              We work alongside your team. We bring senior delivery
              rigor, AI capability, and PMO discipline. We do not run
              your operations, your IT department, or your data
              function for you. If you need full-service outsourcing
              or staff augmentation, hire a different kind of firm.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr />

        <p class="methodology-link">
          The other half of this rigor — how we treat numbers when we
          do quote them — lives on <a href="/methods/cost-of-doing-nothing">/methods/cost-of-doing-nothing</a>.
          Public, dated, sourced.
        </p>

        <p class="closer">
          If you read all of this and still want to talk, that is usually a
          good sign.
        </p>

        <p class="cta-line">
          <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Book a diagnostic</a>
        </p>

        <p class="advisor-nudge">
          Still not sure if you&rsquo;re on the right side of this list?
          <button type="button" class="advisor-inline" data-advisor-open>
            Ask the advisor →
          </button>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose-page {
    padding-top: clamp(40px, 6vh, 72px);
    padding-bottom: clamp(56px, 9vh, 96px);
  }
  .prose-header {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }
  .section-label {
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }
  .h1-page {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(32px, 4.5vw, 48px);
    line-height: 1.16;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    max-width: 22ch;
  }
  .lede {
    font-size: clamp(17px, 2vw, 20px);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.55;
    max-width: 56ch;
  }

  .prose {
    max-width: 760px;
  }
  .rule {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 56px 1fr;
    gap: 20px;
    margin: 36px 0;
    align-items: start;
  }
  .rule-num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--accent-text);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    line-height: 1.4;
    padding-top: 4px;
  }
  .rule h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(20px, 2.4vw, 26px);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 10px;
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
  }
  .rule p {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  .rule-pull {
    margin: 48px 0;
    padding: 24px 28px;
    background: var(--surface-alt);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
  }
  .rule-pull p {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(20px, 2.6vw, 26px);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    line-height: 1.3;
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 30ch;
  }
  .prose hr {
    margin: 40px 0 28px;
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .prose .closer {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 20px;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
  .prose .cta-line {
    margin-top: 8px;
  }
  .methodology-link {
    margin: 28px 0 0;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  .methodology-link a {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .methodology-link a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    text-decoration-color: var(--accent);
  }

  .advisor-nudge {
    margin-top: 32px;
    padding-top: 24px;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  .advisor-inline {
    background: transparent;
    border: none;
    padding: 0;
    font: inherit;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: 500;
    cursor: pointer;
    margin-left: 6px;
  }
  .advisor-inline:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    text-decoration-color: var(--accent);
  }
</style>
